Pitcher Orel Hershiser Retires
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Orel Hershiser, one of baseball's dominant pitchers for
the Los Angeles Dodgers in the 1980s, Thursday announced his retirement.
Hershiser, 41, A three-time All-Star, has a career record of 204-150 with a 3.48
ERA. He was with Cleveland, San Francisco and the New York Mets before returning
to the Dodgers.
</P>
