<HEADLINE> Stocks Higher on Jobless Numbers  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks rose at the start of trading on Wall
Street Friday as investors welcomed the latest indication that the
Federal Reserve is succeeding in its campaign to gently slow down
the economy.
</P>
<P>
   Shortly after Wall Street's opening bell, the Dow Jones
industrial average was up 44.55 at 10,526.02.
</P>
<P>
   Broader stock indicators were also higher. The Standard &AMP; Poor's
