<HEADLINE> Dow Jumps 129; Nasdaq Rises 71  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks rose strongly Friday as investors
welcomed the latest indication that the U.S. economy is slowing
enough to forestall more interest rate hikes. The brightening mood
particularly helped banks and retailers.
</P>
<P>
   In midafternoon trading on Wall Street, the Dow Jones industrial
average was up 129.76 at 10,611.23.
</P>
<P>
   Broader stock indicators were also higher. The Standard &AMP; Poor's
500 index was up 21.91 at 1,478.58, and the Nasdaq composite index
rose 71.19 to 4,031.76.
</P>
<P>
   The Labor Department reported Friday that total employment rose
by only 11,000 in June, the smallest increase in four years. It was
the latest sign that the economy has been cooling in response to a
series of interest rate increases from the Federal Reserve in the
past year.
</P>
<P>
   Investors have been hoping that the Fed may be nearly done with
its current campaign to fight back inflationary pressures and may
be ready to leave rates alone for the next several months.
</P>
<P>
   An improving outlook for interest rates put a glow on financial
companies, which benefit from steady or declining interest rates.
Chase Manhattan rose $1.375 to $49.375, Bank One rose $1.25 to
$30.063 and BankAmerica rose $1.50 to $47.50.
</P>
<P>
   Big retailers also gained with the expectation that steadier
interest rates will fuel consumer buying. Those included Home
Depot, up $3.50 at $54.75, and Wal-Mart, up $3.625 to $60.625.
</P>
<P>
   The positive jobs report helped calm the market, which has been
jittery over the past week ahead of second-quarter earnings
announcements.
</P>
<P>
   Gainers on the stock market Friday included Texas Instruments,
up $2.938 at $70.063; and Gateway, up $5.125 at $62.875.
</P>
<P>
   Qualcomm bucked the upward trend, slipping $4.563 to $57.125 on
a report that Korean wireless operators would not use technology
from the telecom company. Yahoo also slipped $6.688 to $115 as a
brokerage house downgraded the stock, citing concerns about revenue
growth.
</P>
<P>
   Advancing issues outnumbered declining ones by a 3-to-2 margin
on the New York Stock Exchange, where volume came to 632.54 million
shares, up from Thursday's pace.
</P>
<P>
   The Russell 2000 index rose 3.99 to 527.31.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
   On the Net:
</P>
<P>
   New York Stock Exchange: http://www.nyse.com
</P>
<P>
   Nasdaq Stock Market: http://www.nasdaq.com
</P>
</TEXT>
