<HEADLINE> Daily News names new editors, reporters  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   NEW YORK (AP) - Daily News Editor in Chief Ed Kosner announced
several new editorial appointments on Friday.
</P>
<P>
   Teri Thompson, a former Sunday sports editor who left for ESPN
Magazine last year, is rejoining the News as deputy managing
editor/investigations, heading a new three-member sports
investigation unit.
</P>
<P>
   Bob Port, a former reporter for The Associated Press most
recently with apbnews.com, is joining the News as an investigative
reporter.
</P>
<P>
   T.J. Quinn, who covered the Mets for The Record of Hackensack,
in New Jersey, is coming to the News as a baseball writer.
</P>
<P>
   Dick Belsky, a longtime editor at the New York Post and Star
magazine, becomes deputy managing editor.
</P>
<P>
   Melissa Grace, from the Albany Times Union, will cover education
in the Queens bureau, and Greg Gittrich, from the Daily News of Los
Angeles, will do the same in the Bronx.
</P>
<P>
   Graham Fuller, a former executive editor at Interview, will be
the new editor of the News' Showtime section.
</P>
<P>
   Michael Segell, a former editor at Cosmopolitan, will be the new
editor of the Lifeline section.
</P>
<P>
   Lance Gould, who has worked for Glamour, Maxim, Cosmo and Spy,
is the new deputy features editor for arts and entertainment.
</P>
<P>
   Michele Ingrassia, from Newsday, will become a lifestyle
reporter for the News.
</P>
<P>
   Alev Aktar joins the News from Women's Wear Daily as fashion and
beauty editor.
</P>
