<HEADLINE> Latin Grammy Awards Nods Announced  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MIAMI (AP) -- Producer and songwriter Emilio Estefan, teen
heartthrob Marc Anthony and Colombian recording star Shakira led
the nominations Friday for the first Latin Grammy Awards.
</P>
<P>
   Estefan led with six nominations, including producer of the year
for work with his wife, Gloria, and others.
</P>
<P>
   Anthony picked up five nominations. ''Dimelo'' was nominated for
record of the year and song of the year, and he was nominated for
best male pop vocal performance.
</P>
<P>
   Shakira also had five nominations: album of the year, best pop
album, best female pop vocal performance, best female rock vocal
performance and best music video.
</P>
<P>
   The nominations were announced by members of the Latin Academy
and the National Academy of Recording Arts &AMP; Sciences, which hands
out the regular Grammys. The Latin Grammys will be awarded Sept. 13
in Los Angeles.
</P>
<P>
   ''We'll be able to showcase the most important music from Latin
America,'' Estefan said. ''People will start recognizing our
culture and learn.''
</P>
<P>
   Other nominees were Ricky Martin for record of the year for
''Livin' La Vida Loca,'' Santana for best pop instrumental
performance, Christina Aguilera for best pop vocal performance,
Jennifer Lopez and Anthony for best pop performance by a duo, and
Luis Miguel for album of the year.
</P>
<P>
   Winners in 40 categories will be determined by votes cast by
other Latin recording artists.
</P>
<P>
   Pop, rock, salsa, tropical, tejano, norteno, tango, jazz,
classical, merengue, and flamenco and cumbia will be recognized.
</P>
</TEXT>
