<HEADLINE> Business news in brief from around New Jersey  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   FAIRFIELD, N.J. (AP) - Datatec Systems Inc. began trading shares
Friday on the Nasdaq National Market.
</P>
<P>
   The stock trades under the ticker symbol DATC. It had been on
Nasdaq's SmallCap market, but switched to the one reserved for
larger companies.
</P>
<P>
   Isaac J. Gaon, chairman of the networking and e-commerce
company, said he believes the listing will greatly enhance the
company's profile in the investment community. The company's shares
opened at $6.41 Friday.
</P>
<P>
   MADISON, N.J. (AP) - American Home Products Corp. said Friday
that it has appointed Dr. Bruce Burlington to the newly created
position of senior vice president of regulatory affairs and
compliance for the company's drug making division, Wyeth-Ayerst
Pharmaceuticals
</P>
<P>
   Burlington will continue to oversee Wyeth-Ayerst's worldwide
regulatory affairs department, which is responsible for guiding the
company's drug and vaccine development program for the registration
of products. He will assume the additional charge of quality
control for commercial products and research programs. He will
report to Bernard Poussot, president of Wyeth-Ayerst
Pharmaceuticals, and L. Patrick Gage, president of Wyeth-Ayerst
Research.
</P>
<P>
   Burlington joined the company as senior vice president for
global regulatory affairs for pharmaceuticals, vaccines and
biological products last March. Prior to that, he worked for the
U.S. Food and Drug Administration for 17 years, where he most
recently served as director of the FDA's Center for Devices and
Radiological Health.
</P>
<P>
   EATONTOWN, N.J. (AP) - David R. Ammons has been named vice
president of marketing for New World Coffee-Manhattan Bagel Inc.,
the company announced Friday.
</P>
<P>
   Ammons has more than 27 years of experience in advertising and
marketing the food service industry. In his new role, he will
oversee all external and in-store advertising and marketing
programs for the company's four brands, Manhattan Bagel, Chesapeake
Bagel Bakery, New World Coffee and Willoughby's Coffee &AMP; Tea.
</P>
<P>
   KENILWORTH, N.J. (AP) - Maintenance Plus Inc. said Thursday that
it has changed its name to Networking Technologies &AMP; Integration
Inc. and opened a new headquarters in Kenilworth.
</P>
<P>
   Founded in 1985, the company provides hardware maintenance for
mainframe and small computers.
</P>
<P>
   The company said its new name more accurately reflects its core
business, which is the design, implementation and support of local
and wide area computer networks.
</P>
<P>
   OAKLAND, N.J. (AP) - Benjamin Sottile, a former executive at
Gibson Greetings Inc. and the Revlon Cosmetic Group, has been named
vice chairman of Russ Berrie and Co. Inc., the maker of toys and
small gifts announced this week.
</P>
<P>
   Sottile, 62, had been president of Russ Berrie's national
accounts division.
</P>
<P>
   The Oakland-based company also appointed Nicholas Truyens, 51,
vice president and chief financial officer and George DeFuria, 50,
vice president and chief information officer.
</P>
</TEXT>
