<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that were moving substantially or trading
heavily Friday on the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq Stock
Market.
</P>
<P>
NYSE
</P>
<P>
Chase Manhattan, up $2.063 at $50.063.
</P>
<P>
   Financial stocks rose following a report showing a modest
increase in job growth in June, suggesting that the Fed has been
succeeding in slowing the economy and may be nearing the end of its
inflation-fighting campaign of raising interest rates.
</P>
<P>
Merrill Lynch, down $0.813 at $123.25
</P>
<P>
   The Wall Street Journal reports that the major brokerage house
may cut 2,000 jobs. Separately, Deutsche Bank denies rumors that it
intends to buy the company.
</P>
<P>
Corning, up $7.188 at $256.688
</P>
<P>
   The leading maker of fiber-optic cable plans to add as many as
100 workers at four plants as its business expands, marking the
first addition of union workers to its payrolls in six years.
</P>
<P>
NASDAQ
</P>
<P>
Yahoo, down $5.875 at $116.5
</P>
<P>
   Deutsche Banc Alex. Brown cuts its rating on the stock, citing
concerns about revenue growth and high valuations.
</P>
<P>
Qualcomm, down $5.063 at $56.625
</P>
<P>
   Shares of the telecom equipment maker fell on rumors that major
Korean wireless companies won't use Qualcomm's products.
</P>
<P>
PeopleSoft, up $2.50 at $18.375
</P>
<P>
   Lehman Brothers upgrades the maker of human resources software
to outperfrom from neutral.
</P>
