<HEADLINE> Mailman injured by falling second-floor AC unit  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   ATLANTIC CITY, N.J. (AP) - A letter carrier suffered a cut on
his head when an air conditioning unit fell from a second-story
window and landed on him, authorities said.
</P>
<P>
   Robert Salvo, 26, was knocked to the ground when the
window-mounted air conditioner dropped 11 feet onto his head as he
delivered mail to an apartment Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   ''He's going to be fine,'' said Postmaster Harry Morgan. ''He
has to get some stitches on his head, though.''
</P>
<P>
   Salvo was discharged Friday from Atlantic City Medical Center,
where he was treated and then held for observation. He declined
requests for an interview, hospital spokeswoman Jennifer Tornetta
said.
</P>
<P>
   Salvo, who has worked for the Postal Service for two years, was
working as a replacement carrier when the accident happened. It was
his first day on the route, Morgan said.
</P>
</TEXT>
