<HEADLINE> Pirates' Anderson Sent to Minors  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   PITTSBURGH (AP) -- Pittsburgh Pirates left-hander Jimmy Anderson,
who beat the Cubs on Wednesday for his first victory since April
15, was optioned Friday to Double-A Altoona.
</P>
<P>
   Taking Anderson's spot on the roster is outfielder Chad
Hermansen, who began the season as the starting center fielder but
was later demoted to Triple-A Nashville.
</P>
<P>
   The move is only temporary. The Pirates want to keep Anderson on
his regular throwing schedule during the All-Star break, especially
since right-hander Francisco Cordova will miss at least one start
with a sore elbow.
</P>
<P>
   Right-hander Bronson Arroyo was optioned to Nashville last week
for the same reason. Anderson will return to the Pirates next
weekend in Cleveland and Arroyo may, too, especially if Cordova's
injury forces him to go on the disabled list.
</P>
<P>
   Anderson will start Monday for Altoona. He would have been sent
to Nashville, except the Sounds aren't scheduled that day.
</P>
<P>
   ''It's very important that Jimmy be ready to pitch,'' general
manager Cam Bonifay said.
</P>
<P>
   Hermansen hit .243 with six home runs and 23 RBIs with
Nashville. With Adrian Brown (hamstring) likely to miss the entire
weekend series against Minnesota, the Pirates wanted another
outfielder on their roster.
</P>
</TEXT>
