<HEADLINE> Boy accidentally shoots 12-year-old sister in leg  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   ALTONA, N.Y. (AP) A 12-year-old girl was injured when her
brother accidentally shot her in the leg with a .44-caliber black
powder pistol.
</P>
<P>
   Raelyn Ostrander was shot in the thigh Thursday morning as her
13-year-old brother handled the pistol in their home. The bullet
passed through her leg and out a window.
</P>
<P>
   She was treated and released from a local hospital.
</P>
<P>
   The shooting comes at a time of increased national attention on
gun control.
</P>
<P>
   Federal statistics show guns are in about half of all U.S.
households. According to the Center for Disease Control and
Prevention, five children died every day in firearm-related
accidents and suicides from 1990 to 1997.
</P>
<P>
   The state Legislature this year passed tougher gun regulations
including requiring trigger locks on new guns sold and raising the
age of legal ownership from 18 to 21.
</P>
<P>
   Also, more than 100 cities around the nation have handed out
free locks to help reduce the chance of an accidental discharge.
</P>
<P>
   Altona is in Clinton County, 154 miles north of Albany and 10
miles south of the Canadian border.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
