<HEADLINE> Sol 49, Rockers 46  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MIAMI (AP) -- Sharon Manning scored 13 points and Marlies Askamp
had eight rebounds as the Miami Sol beat the Cleveland Rockers
49-46 Friday night.
</P>
<P>
   The Sol held off a late charge by the Rockers when Askamp's
basket with 2:57 remaining gave Miami a 44-43 lead.
</P>
<P>
   Katrina Colleton and Kristen Rasmussen both made two free to
extend the lead to 48-43 with 25 seconds left in the game.
Cleveland's Merlakia Jones hit a 3-pointer with 15.6 seconds left
to close the gap to 48-46.
</P>
<P>
   Milena Flores' free throw with 12 seconds remaining closed out
the scoring, as Miami (6-11) won at home for the first time since
beating Cleveland on June 17.
</P>
<P>
   Askamp and Colleton added nine points each for the Sol.
</P>
<P>
   The Rockers (8-8) struggled without starting forward Eva
Nemcova, out for the season after tearing her anterior cruciate
ligament at Los Angeles last Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   Mery Andrade led Cleveland with 10 points, and Chastity Melvin
and Jones added nine each.
</P>
<P>
   The Rockers led 27-22 with 4:05 left in the first half, but the
Sol went on a 9-0 run to take a four-point lead at halftime.
</P>
<P>
   The Rockers jumped out to a 7-0 lead to start the game, but the
Sol took its first lead five minutes into the half after Askamp
tied the game with a lay-up and sank a subsequent foul shot that
made the score 10-9.
</P>
</TEXT>
