<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Covered by blanket, body found in culvert  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   BETHLEHEM, N.Y. (AP) - Police are investigating the murder of a
state worker whose body was found Friday face down in a culvert,
covered with a blanket.
</P>
<P>
   The body of 47-year-old Cecil Nellenback was found by a town
highway crew at 1:50 p.m., clothed in shorts, short-sleeve shirt
and tennis shoes, police said. He died of severe head injuries,
according to the Albany City Police Department, which is conducting
a joint investigation with town of Bethlehem police.
</P>
<P>
   The body was in an advanced state of decomposition.
</P>
<P>
   Albany police spokesman Det. James Miller said it appeared
Nellenback was murdered somewhere else.
</P>
<P>
   ''More than likely he was dumped there,'' Miller said. ''It's
kind of an isolated road.''
</P>
<P>
   Bethlehem is five miles southwest of Albany.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-ES-07-07-00 2222 </TRAILER>
</DOC>
