as the New York Liberty beat the Minnesota Lynx 76-70 Friday night.
</P>
<P>
   Phillips, the WNBA player of the week, recorded her eighth
double-double of the season -- and fifth in seven games -- as she
equaled her career high in rebounds.
</P>
<P>
   The Liberty (9-9), trailing 33-30 at halftime, opened the second
half with 8-for-9 shooting to take the lead for good at 49-43.
Phillips scored eight points during the run.
</P>
