   Minnesota's Betty Lennox, a candidate for rookie of the year,
hit a 3-pointer to cut the deficit to 69-67 with 2:15 left.
However, Becky Hammon's layup with 1:27 remaining, and Teresa
Weatherspoon's free throw about a minute later restored the
Liberty's five-point lead.
</P>
<P>
   Minnesota's Katy Smith, the league's leading scorer with a
21.4-point average, scored 12 of her 16 points in the first half as
the Lynx lost their second straight at home.
</P>
<P>
   The Lynx (10-7) jumped off to a 9-0 lead, with Smith scoring
seven points. Lennox had her second double-double with 20 points,
and added a career-high 12 rebounds.
</P>
<P>
   Reserve Sue Wicks had nine points and 10 rebounds for the
Liberty, winners of four of six.
</P>
